<span class=3D"h2"><a class=3D"selflink" id=3D"section-12" href=3D"https://=
www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc8410#section-12">12</a>.  Security Considerations=
</span>

   The security considerations of [<a href=3D"https://www.rfc-editor.org/rf=
c/rfc5280" title=3D"&quot;Internet X.509 Public Key Infrastructure Certific=
ate and Certificate Revocation List (CRL) Profile&quot;">RFC5280</a>], [<a =
href=3D"https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc7748" title=3D"&quot;Elliptic Cur=
ves for Security&quot;">RFC7748</a>], and [<a href=3D"https://www.rfc-edito=
r.org/rfc/rfc8032" title=3D"&quot;Edwards-Curve Digital Signature Algorithm=
 (EdDSA)&quot;">RFC8032</a>]
   apply accordingly.

   The procedures for going from a private key to a public key are
   different when used with Diffie-Hellman versus when used with Edwards
   Signatures.  This means that the same public key cannot be used for
   both ECDH and EdDSA.








